If only artificial soft items are available, combining two 'artificial, soft, cut' items gives 50. Scissors are single-use. message: To reach 100, focus on soft items. First, use scissors on ONE natural soft ingredient (e.g., flower, sunflower, feather) and ONE artificial soft ingredient (e.g., paper, sponge, ribbon, thread, newspaper). This will give you two 'cut' items with value 25 each. Next, combine these two *cut* items (one natural, one artificial). This unique combination will create an item with value 80. Finally, use the frame tool on this 80-value combined item to reach 100. Avoid cutting or framing hard items, and do not combine more than two items, especially if they are already framed, as this quickly leads to negative values and 'ruined frame' features which cannot be fixed.
